 plain, black robe and armor, you could tell he was inhumanly strong, solid, and agile all at the same time.  His tail trailed behind him, the only thing that gave him away as an Iksar, not dragged along the ground, but carried along with pride.  The helmet and mask he wore covered all his face except for two slits from which his eyes glared out, deep blue and cold as ice.  A mace with its head carved like a skull and an ornate velium hand axe dangled by his waist, his hands right beside them.  There was no mistaking the Warlord, and few ever underestimated him.<br>
<br>
Those who did didn't last long enough to repeat the mistake.<br>
<br>
As he walked up to the door, his glare settled on one of the guards.  In an instant, he forgot his orders, frozen in his place with terror.  Saurix remained perfectly calm, and at the same time very much ready to spring into action.  He hadn't come expecting a very warm reception.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Bring me your leader, or the half-breed, whichever you can find first.  I have a few pieces of peaceful business I wish to attend to.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>After a few seconds, the guard had still shown no reaction.  Saurix, unimpressed and getting annoyed, focused his glare even further and added, more forcefully</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Do not waste my time, soft skin.  Go.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>With that, the guard finally snapped out of his fearful trance.  He hadn't heard the instructions, but didn't want to stand around any longer, and ran inside the keep to find someone to talk to this Iksar in his place.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=137021">Veteran Saurix Shizathir</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
