<br>
Two things, simple things, that is all.  So simple that even one such as yourself should be able to get them done.  And it would, of course, be detrimental to your cause to refuse.  No bloodshed - for now, of course - if you do as I say, you have my word.<br>
<br>
One, you must find someone in your..  organization, who is on decent enough terms with the Kromzek, to preform a simple task for me.<br>
<br>
Two, you will see to it that those in and involved with your little band are notified of their impending doom, so that they understand more fully the risks of leaving this place.  Fair enough, yes?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>With that, Saurix waited for the Enforcer's response, still wishing he were almost anywhere but here.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
